cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE

This paper is about a new algorithm for training deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The algorithm is designed for distributed systems, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper specifically tests the algorithm on the ImageNet classification task, which is a computer vision (cs.CV) problem. Finally, the paper is focused on improving the efficiency of training, which is a common goal in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
